Question: Partition employees into those earning above $5,000 and those earning $5,000 or less.

Input:
List of Employee objects with a getSalary() method.

Solutions:-

Java 8 Streams partition employees by salary threshold using Collectors.partitioningBy(e -> e.getSalary() > 5000). Returns Map<Boolean, List<Employee>> where true=above $5K, false=≤$5K.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream employee list → collect(partitioningBy(salary > 5000)) → Access via get(true)/get(false).

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.*;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

class Employee {
    private String name;
    private double salary;
    
    public Employee(String name, double salary) {
        this.name = name;
        this.salary = salary;
    }
    
    public String getName() { return name; }
    public double getSalary() { return salary; }
    
    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return name + " ($" + salary + ")";
    }
}

public class SalaryPartition {
    public static Map<Boolean, List<Employee>> partitionBySalary(List<Employee> employees) {
        return employees.stream()
                       .collect(Collectors.partitioningBy(e -> e.getSalary() > 5000));
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Employee> employees = Arrays.asList(
            new Employee("Alice", 6000),
            new Employee("Bob", 4500),
            new Employee("Charlie", 7000),
            new Employee("Diana", 4000)
        );
        
        Map<Boolean, List<Employee>> partitioned = partitionBySalary(employees);
        
        System.out.println("Above $5K: " + partitioned.get(true));
        System.out.println("≤ $5K: " + partitioned.get(false));
    }
}

Output:
text
Above $5K: [Alice ($6000.0), Charlie ($7000.0)]
≤ $5K: [Bob ($4500.0), Diana ($4000.0)]

#Thought Process
partitioningBy creates boolean-keyed Map (always true/false keys). Single-pass O(n). Predicate salary > 5000 strict (5000 goes to false). Default toList() downstream collector.

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: {true=[], false=[]}
All above: {true=[all], false=[]}
All ≤5000: {true=[], false=[all]}
Exactly 5000: false (≤5000)
Null list: NPE on stream()
Null salary: NPE in predicate

